text: Argodrepana denticulata is a moth in the family Drepanidae. It was described by Wilkinson in 1967. It is widely distributed in Indonesian New Guinea.The Hooktips (Drepanidae, Drepaninae) of Papua Indonesia ==References== Category:Moths described in 1967 Category:Drepaninae Category:Moths of New Guinea
title: Argodrepana denticulata
